description: We train AI to do fun things! Everything on the channel was created specifically for this channel (using Unity), so this is the only place you'll be able to find these kinds of videos :)

Subscribe for AI insights, guides, new techniques, courses, and more...

I am Louis-François (or just Louis, loo·ee, French pronunciation), from Montreal, Canada, also known as "What's AI", co-founder of Towards AI, and ex-PhD student at Mila.

Focused on making AI accessible. I aim to demystify the AI “black box” for everyone and sensitize people about its potential and risks.

I also publish articles on my blog every week if you enjoy short reads: https://www.louisbouchard.ai/, and have my updates on the newsletter https://louisbouchard.substack.com/.

Follow @whats_ai on Instagram, Twitter, and connect on LinkedIn! Come exchange with me and follow my projects!

►Join our discord server with many other AI enthusiasts: https://www.louisbouchard.ai/learn-ai-together/
►If you'd like to support me, I have a Patreon where you can do that: https://www.patreon.com/whatsai

Want to achieve more cinematic look in your AI videos? AI Filmmaking Academy is a branch of FILM ART AI LLC. It's the first place where you can learn this directly from professional Directors of Photography (DoPs), cinematographers, filmmakers and film directors who have mastered the use of AI video generating. Here you will discover how to adopt the principles of cinematography to create stunning cinematic AI videos that will win AI filmmaking competitions and allow you to make money on your passion. We offer expert tutorials on how to utilize top-class cinematic composition, lighting, framing, and camera storytelling in your AI movies. 

You’ll learn how to apply principles of cinematography to achieve a cinematic look and impressive visual storytelling in your AI videos, regardless of the AI video generator you use. 

Disclaimer: In videos testing AI video generators, we we use footage generated by ourselves exclusively. 

Subscribe and start creating amazing AI movies today!
Build Your AI Toolkit: Practical Tutorials & Weekly Updates You'll Actually Use

Videos about Artificial Intelligence Safety Research, for everyone.

AI is leaping forward right now, it's only a matter of time before we develop true Artificial General Intelligence, and there are a lot of different ways that this could go badly wrong for us. Putting aside the science fiction, this channel is about AI Safety research - humanity's best attempt to foresee the problems AI might pose and work out ways to ensure that our AI developments are safe and beneficial.
